    3.4 Gost HTTPS

    gost HTTPS Web

    gost Docker gost 

    #!/bin/bash

# 
DOMAIN="YOU.DOMAIN.NAME"
USER="username"
PASS="password"
PORT=443

BIND_IP=0.0.0.0
CERT_DIR=/etc/letsencrypt
CERT=${CERT_DIR}/live/${DOMAIN}/fullchain.pem
KEY=${CERT_DIR}/live/${DOMAIN}/privkey.pem
sudo docker run -d --name gost \
    -v ${CERT_DIR}:${CERT_DIR}:ro \
    --net=host ginuerzh/gost \
    -L "http2://${USER}:${PASS}@${BIND_IP}:${PORT}?cert=${CERT}&key=${KEY}&probe_resist=code:404&knock=www.google.com"

    (DOMAIN), (USER), (PASS) (PORT)

    gost Gost Wiki probe_resist=code:404 404probe_resist=file:/path/to/file.txt probe_resist=web:example.com/page.html

SS_PORT=1984
SS_PASSWD=MyPasswd

sudo docker run -dt --name ss \
   -p ${SS_PORT}:${SS_PORT} mritd/shadowsocks \
